    "summary": {
      "overall_summary": {
        "value": "Boone, NC presents a compelling relocation destination for those seeking a small-town mountain lifestyle in an elevated Appalachian setting with a young, educated, and safe community. The area's 3,333-foot elevation minimizes hurricane and seismic risks, while a strong 90.3-rated school district and nearby Appalachian State University make it attractive for families and young professionals\u2014reflected in its unusually low median age of 24.5 years and above-average violent crime safety index of 72. Moderate housing costs around $517,500 paired with low electricity rates of 8.68 cents/kWh and a lean 4.99% state income tax support affordability, though the 112-day growing season and low sunshine (200 days annually) may challenge agricultural interests and mood-sensitive individuals. While the area benefits from reasonable regional connectivity to Asheville and Greensboro and a vibrant food/beverage economy focused on tourism and local farmers markets, prospective residents should weigh the trade-offs of limited major retail chains, moderate drought vulnerability requiring potential water restrictions, and dependence on nearby metros for specialized services. Boone works best for those prioritizing community, outdoor access, education, and affordability over climate diversity, urban amenities, and extensive sunshine.",
        "source_url": null,
        "fetched_date": null,
        "status": "valid",
        "schema_version": 1
      }
    }
